modules.description: Implements precise time-based blocking operations, allowing code to suspend execution for a specified duration in nanoseconds. Works with integer values representing time intervals and integrates with Lwt for asynchronous workflow management. Useful for implementing delays in network protocols or timing-sensitive distributed system operations.

This module enables precise time-based blocking operations using nanosecond-resolution delays, integrated with Lwt for asynchronous execution. It provides functions to suspend computation for specified durations, supporting integer-based time intervals. Operations are designed for use in network protocols and timing-sensitive distributed systems. For example, it can introduce controlled delays in message transmission or manage timed retries in asynchronous workflows.
